WEBVTT

00:15.625 --> 00:16.417
♪ (MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:16.875 --> 00:17.834
CHARLIE BAUDELAIRE:
No heroin shipment ever came in.

00:17.917 --> 00:21.083
Who knew about it?
You, me, and Jett.

00:21.792 --> 00:22.583
HENRY: Vicky.

00:22.875 --> 00:24.542
You in some kind of trouble
in here, Henry?

00:24.750 --> 00:26.834
-(GUN SHOTS)
-MAN: What are you doing?

00:26.917 --> 00:28.750
-(GRUNTS)
-EVANS:
Mr. Bestic is very pleased

00:28.834 --> 00:30.291
with the way
you handle obstacles.

00:30.875 --> 00:33.083
There's another duffle
in my car with the same amount

00:33.166 --> 00:35.375
if you agree to handle
Nolan and his nurse.

00:35.458 --> 00:38.250
Tell your boss I'm a thief.
That's what I'm good at.

00:38.333 --> 00:40.250
I really need to discuss
something with you.

00:40.333 --> 00:41.417
Fuck off.

00:41.750 --> 00:42.750
Forever.

00:42.959 --> 00:44.125
Leave my family alone.

00:44.500 --> 00:46.542
JACKIE DILLON:
Junior and Silas have been
spending time together.

00:46.625 --> 00:48.000
Why don't you bust Junior
already?

00:48.250 --> 00:50.166
-(PHONE VIBRATES)
-Hello?

00:50.250 --> 00:52.375
EVANS:
Before you go in there, there's
something you oughta know.

00:52.458 --> 00:53.709
(CHAINSAW BUZZES)

00:53.792 --> 00:56.083
WOMAN:
You've got that look
in your eyes tonight.

00:56.458 --> 00:57.834
Like you're mad at God.

00:58.125 --> 00:59.000
I know you?

00:59.250 --> 01:01.083
If you've got any sense
of self-preservation,

01:01.166 --> 01:03.709
I recommend you pick up
your clothes and hurry inside.

01:03.792 --> 01:05.333
What'll you do
if I come over there?

01:05.417 --> 01:07.500
-Really lousy--
-(GUNSHOTS)

01:11.000 --> 01:13.458
-♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
-(GUNSHOT)

01:24.250 --> 01:28.750
-(electric saw whining)
-(hammer tapping)

01:31.417 --> 01:34.458
(men chattering
in Spanish outside)

01:34.542 --> 01:36.500
(dog barking)

01:39.959 --> 01:41.583
(gasps, pants)

01:48.166 --> 01:50.041
Phoenix:
I dropped Alice off early
for her field trip.

01:50.125 --> 01:51.583
When did they
start remodeling?

01:51.667 --> 01:54.375
-Huh?
-The garage, next door.

01:57.000 --> 01:58.667
(door opens)

01:58.750 --> 02:00.291
What the fuck did I miss?

02:00.375 --> 02:03.542
(speaking Spanish)

02:04.959 --> 02:08.583
Hey! (speaking Spanish)

02:11.000 --> 02:11.959
Distract them.

02:12.041 --> 02:13.417
-What?
-Keep them out here.

02:13.500 --> 02:14.834
-How?
-Improvise!

02:15.709 --> 02:17.792
-Uh, excuse me. Hi.
-Hi.

02:17.875 --> 02:19.583
Phoenix:
Hello...

02:21.125 --> 02:22.250
(clattering)

02:22.333 --> 02:24.083
You guys
like nipples?

02:24.166 --> 02:25.291
(speaking Spanish)

02:25.375 --> 02:27.542
(indistinct chatter)

02:29.417 --> 02:31.041
Phoenix:
What's nipples
in Spanish?

02:37.208 --> 02:40.000
(speaking Spanish)

02:40.083 --> 02:42.959
(laughter)

02:51.417 --> 02:54.375
(laughter, chatter)

02:54.458 --> 02:55.542
No, no, no.

02:55.625 --> 02:57.041
Workers:
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

02:57.125 --> 02:58.500
What's
going on?

02:58.583 --> 02:59.667
What?

02:59.750 --> 03:01.458
(speaking Spanish)

03:01.542 --> 03:04.000
(chattering)

03:04.083 --> 03:06.792
What? You're not
homos, are you?

03:07.291 --> 03:09.208
(men speaking Spanish)

03:10.083 --> 03:11.000
Man:
Oh!

03:11.083 --> 03:13.250
What are you doing?

03:14.166 --> 03:15.000
Mandy!

03:15.083 --> 03:17.583
What the hell is
wrong with you?

03:17.667 --> 03:19.750
Come on!
(huffs)

03:20.458 --> 03:23.166
I'm so sorry.
She is in therapy
for this, you know?

03:23.250 --> 03:25.667
Well, you got to keep her
away from my workers.
They'll never finish.

03:25.750 --> 03:30.500
-Oh, pfft! Don't be racist--
-Get! Get in the house! Sorry.

03:30.583 --> 03:32.834
You're in so much trouble,
young lady!

03:32.917 --> 03:34.625
(speaking Spanish)

03:34.709 --> 03:36.500
(laughing)

03:39.458 --> 03:42.041
(laughing)

03:52.750 --> 03:54.166
So, how much is
in there?

03:54.250 --> 03:57.125
-What do you know about it?
-Jett told me.

03:57.834 --> 04:00.667
Best place to hide money
is other people's houses.

04:00.750 --> 04:02.291
-She told you that?
-Mm-hmm.

04:02.375 --> 04:05.500
It's the only important detail
she ever actually told me,

04:05.583 --> 04:07.875
and it took me a year
to get it out of her.

04:07.959 --> 04:10.208
Everybody else spent all day,
in the yard, telling stories

04:10.291 --> 04:12.417
about what they did
and how they fucked up.

04:12.500 --> 04:14.917
I'd listen because some of
the stories were really funny,

04:15.000 --> 04:17.041
even if you'd
heard them before.

04:17.125 --> 04:19.375
Some of those girls
could've done stand-up.

04:19.834 --> 04:21.375
-Not her.
-No.

04:21.458 --> 04:24.333
-She doesn't joke much.
-Why is that?

04:24.417 --> 04:26.709
Nothing's usually that funny.

04:26.792 --> 04:29.375
-(door opens)
-Speak of the devil.

04:29.458 --> 04:30.834
Hey!

04:30.917 --> 04:32.417
-I already missed her?
-Maria: Yeah.

04:32.500 --> 04:34.583
She has
a field trip today.

04:34.667 --> 04:36.417
How'd your thing go?

04:36.500 --> 04:39.917
-What thing?
-The thing you went
out of town for.

04:40.000 --> 04:41.542
Everything
work out?

04:41.625 --> 04:43.250
Phoenix says you told her

04:43.333 --> 04:45.917
hiding money in other people's
houses is a good idea.

04:46.000 --> 04:47.166
I don't remember saying that.

04:47.250 --> 04:50.583
Yes! Yes, you did.
Do you remember Rochelle?

04:52.709 --> 04:55.500
-Big girl?
-Three hundred pounds.
Hornier than--

04:56.375 --> 04:58.041
What's something super horny?

05:00.041 --> 05:01.917
An Andalusian goat
with two cocks.

05:02.000 --> 05:04.625
Hornier than an Andalusian
goat with two cocks.

05:04.709 --> 05:06.750
Had to keep reminding
her she was a girl

05:06.834 --> 05:08.250
every time she looked my way.

05:08.333 --> 05:11.083
This seems to be a running
problem you have.

05:11.166 --> 05:13.166
Rochelle robbed a bank,
high on crack, made 500 bucks.

05:13.250 --> 05:16.458
That's her. Okay,
so she was telling us
that story for the fourth time,

05:16.542 --> 05:19.917
and then you told me
about hiding money
in other people's houses.

05:20.709 --> 05:22.333
Maybe I did.

05:22.417 --> 05:25.542
So? What's in the bag?

05:28.959 --> 05:30.542
Here.

05:30.625 --> 05:32.583
Sixty-two thousand.

05:33.458 --> 05:35.667
What am I supposed
to do with it?

05:35.750 --> 05:38.542
Rent us a house for the year,
put it under Maria's name.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.542
-Really?
-Mm-hmm. But don't
be tacky about it.

05:42.625 --> 05:44.750
I'm not tacky.
Do you think I'm tacky?

05:44.834 --> 05:47.667
I meant ostentatious.
Just pick something
functional,

05:47.750 --> 05:49.333
with good light, off the street,

05:49.417 --> 05:51.166
but near the hospital
and Alice's school.

05:51.250 --> 05:54.083
Okay, well, there's
decisions to be made.

05:54.166 --> 05:56.208
Yard, no yard,
pool, Spanish tile,

05:56.291 --> 05:58.959
-modern, what do you like?
-I got to take a shower.

06:04.792 --> 06:06.291
We trust you.

06:07.041 --> 06:09.125
(doorbell rings)

06:10.458 --> 06:14.208
Jett. Oh...
Did I wake you?

06:14.291 --> 06:16.917
No. What-- what
brings you here?

06:17.000 --> 06:19.750
I knew I should've called ahead,
but, uh, I was out and about,

06:19.834 --> 06:22.458
and I wondered if you'd come
for a ride with me.

06:22.542 --> 06:24.333
If you're not too busy?

06:27.333 --> 06:29.792
Well, I was just
making coffee.

06:29.875 --> 06:31.917
I haven't even put
my makeup on yet.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.250
Oh, well,
you look terrific.

06:34.333 --> 06:37.041
Indulge me.
It shouldn't take too long.

06:38.125 --> 06:40.125
Let me get my purse.

06:49.375 --> 06:51.208
Phoenix:
You okay?

06:55.375 --> 06:56.959
(mutters):
Fuck.

06:57.792 --> 06:59.875
♪ ♪

07:00.750 --> 07:04.250
My old Army buddy,
Jacques McCabe,
I think I told you about him.

07:04.333 --> 07:06.417
-Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.
-Tour guide down in the Keys.

07:06.500 --> 07:09.750
Yeah, he once told me
that he's convinced

07:09.834 --> 07:11.709
that women have no honor.

07:12.625 --> 07:14.834
What do you think
about that?

07:14.917 --> 07:17.375
I think he probably got fucked
over by more than one woman,

07:17.458 --> 07:19.875
and he had enough,
quit trying to figure them out.

07:19.959 --> 07:21.959
Hmm. Certainly part of it.

07:22.041 --> 07:23.792
Feels like they say
one thing to your face,

07:23.875 --> 07:25.709
and they'll keep saying it
as long as it provides them

07:25.792 --> 07:27.583
with the comforts
they feel they deserve,

07:27.667 --> 07:29.333
but as soon as
you're not looking,

07:29.417 --> 07:32.667
they find somebody else,
upgrade.

07:33.166 --> 07:35.250
This, he claims, is
their nature.

07:35.333 --> 07:37.417
They're
practical creatures.

07:37.500 --> 07:38.917
There you go.

07:39.041 --> 07:42.250
But honor is
an abstract concept.

07:42.333 --> 07:45.875
It's not a practical
thing, is it?

07:45.959 --> 07:47.625
No, it isn't.

07:47.709 --> 07:49.542
But women are
practical beings.

07:49.625 --> 07:53.917
I mean, we must admit.
I mean, they have to be
to keep the species going.

07:54.000 --> 07:55.959
What are we talking
about, Charlie?

07:56.041 --> 07:57.291
It's like in chess.

07:57.375 --> 08:00.041
You can figure out as many
moves ahead as you like,

08:00.125 --> 08:02.667
because none of
the pieces are moving,
they're all frozen in place.

08:02.750 --> 08:05.417
But in the real world,
you can figure out

08:05.500 --> 08:08.875
maybe two, three moves
ahead, tops,

08:08.959 --> 08:12.000
because everything is
in constant motion.

08:12.083 --> 08:15.375
-You follow what I'm saying?
-Sure, like driving in traffic.

08:15.458 --> 08:19.375
Exactly.
You're watching two,
three cars ahead of you,

08:19.458 --> 08:22.125
but if you were to analyze
and anticipate

08:22.208 --> 08:24.583
what everybody might do,
I mean...

08:25.417 --> 08:28.375
All the different combinations,
I mean, phew!

08:28.458 --> 08:31.667
Confusion ensues,
and you end up crashing.

08:32.625 --> 08:34.417
It's chaos.

08:35.417 --> 08:38.250
Hmm. How'd we get to traffic?

08:38.333 --> 08:40.417
-Honor.
-Ah, yeah.

08:40.959 --> 08:45.000
I think you're someone
who understands honor

08:45.083 --> 08:48.291
because it doesn't
embarrass you
to talk about it.

08:48.375 --> 08:50.667
You're someone
who gives your word,

08:50.750 --> 08:52.709
and you keep it.

08:52.792 --> 08:55.000
And yet something
is worrying you.

08:56.125 --> 08:58.000
You and I,

08:58.083 --> 09:00.333
we spent a lot of time
together throughout the years

09:00.417 --> 09:02.667
getting sweaty
and serious.

09:02.750 --> 09:04.542
(inhales)

09:04.625 --> 09:06.750
Or am I wrong?

09:09.667 --> 09:13.375
Have we or have we not
been getting serious?

09:15.375 --> 09:17.208
This isn't where you
tell me you and your wife

09:17.291 --> 09:18.792
are married in name only,

09:18.875 --> 09:20.959
sleep in separate beds, is it?

09:21.041 --> 09:23.375
-'Cause I already knew that.
-No.

09:23.458 --> 09:25.583
This is where I tell you
I used to know what
you were up to,

09:25.667 --> 09:28.875
but lately, not so much.

09:28.959 --> 09:30.375
For instance,

09:30.458 --> 09:31.917
you don't work
at the bar anymore.

09:32.000 --> 09:33.375
And you tell me
that Quinn's in Mexico,

09:33.458 --> 09:34.875
but I can't get
anybody to find him.

09:34.959 --> 09:36.750
Wasn't aware you
were looking for him.

09:36.834 --> 09:38.792
That's not the point.

09:38.875 --> 09:40.375
(sighs)

09:40.458 --> 09:42.625
Jett, your main asset is
you do your job

09:42.709 --> 09:44.875
without calling a lot
of attention to yourself.

09:44.959 --> 09:46.208
That's your style.

09:46.291 --> 09:48.500
In that sense,
we're two peas in a pod.

09:49.250 --> 09:53.291
Of course, you have other,
more specialized assets.

09:53.375 --> 09:56.750
Christ.
The way you
move in bed,

09:56.834 --> 09:59.750
-you could be a pro.
-Why are you trying
to provoke me?

09:59.834 --> 10:02.250
Did I touch a nerve?

10:02.333 --> 10:04.166
It was meant as a compliment.

10:04.250 --> 10:05.583
It just didn't come out right.

10:05.667 --> 10:08.583
Get to the point
or drop me off.

10:08.667 --> 10:10.417
-(window partition opening)
-I'm getting carsick.

10:10.500 --> 10:11.583
-Bennie: Boss.
-Not now.

10:11.667 --> 10:12.625
I'm so sorry, it's your wife.

10:12.709 --> 10:14.291
(sighs) Can she hear me?

10:14.375 --> 10:16.792
-No, it's on mute.
-Bennie, why would
I wanna talk to my wife?

10:16.875 --> 10:18.375
She sounds frantic.

10:18.458 --> 10:21.083
-Charlie: What,
she miss a sample sale?
-It's about Junior.

10:21.166 --> 10:23.125
(Charlie sighs)

10:25.750 --> 10:27.458
Vivian?

10:27.542 --> 10:28.458
Yes.

10:28.542 --> 10:29.667
Mm-hmm.

10:31.250 --> 10:33.291
I'm on my way. (sighs)

10:33.375 --> 10:35.542
I said I'm on my way.

10:36.083 --> 10:38.959
-Bennie, take us home.
-You got it.

10:39.041 --> 10:42.291
-This won't take but a minute.
-(partition closes)

11:23.083 --> 11:24.542
He's locked himself
in your study.

11:24.625 --> 11:26.458
I'm pretty sure he's
blowing rails in there.

11:26.542 --> 11:29.125
He shoved a gun
in Billy's face.

11:29.208 --> 11:31.417
Nearly scared
the poor soul to death.

11:31.500 --> 11:33.709
-Who's Billy?
-It's Wednesday.

11:34.750 --> 11:36.125
Billy
my yoga instructor.

11:36.208 --> 11:37.709
He's probably
never coming back.

11:37.792 --> 11:39.625
Who are you?

11:39.709 --> 11:41.000
What is my rule
about you bringing

11:41.083 --> 11:42.500
your women
into my home?

11:42.583 --> 11:45.083
-She's my lawyer.
-(scoffs) Your lawyer.

11:47.250 --> 11:50.375
Huh. I understand lawyers
can be disbarred for lying.

11:50.458 --> 11:52.750
Isn't that right?
So, tell me.

11:52.834 --> 11:54.333
Are you
fucking him?

11:54.417 --> 11:56.667
No. Are you?

11:56.750 --> 12:00.125
Get your degenerate
fuckwit son out of my house!

12:01.750 --> 12:02.959
(snorts)

12:04.959 --> 12:07.959
Dad. Did you see the two guys
in the Seville out there?

12:08.041 --> 12:09.417
-No, I didn't.
-You didn't?

12:09.500 --> 12:11.542
-I saw them.
-Junior: Okay.

12:11.625 --> 12:14.375
They're mine.
It's all good. Good.

12:14.458 --> 12:15.834
Wh-What are you
doing here?

12:15.917 --> 12:17.875
I'm regrouping is what.

12:17.959 --> 12:20.542
I mean, you always say come
to you. First, come to you,

12:20.625 --> 12:22.417
so I'm here.

12:22.500 --> 12:24.709
-Somebody's following me.
-Who's following you?

12:24.792 --> 12:28.125
Well, Dad, if I knew,
I'd hit 'em, right?

12:28.208 --> 12:29.250
Hey, Jett.

12:29.333 --> 12:31.625
-Why don't I wait outside?
-No, stay.

12:34.667 --> 12:35.750
They got Wesley.

12:35.834 --> 12:36.834
-Taggart?
-Mm.

12:36.917 --> 12:38.291
That's why I got
the reinforcements.

12:38.375 --> 12:40.166
But, you know,
these guys come recommended.

12:40.250 --> 12:42.291
Hopper did time with one of
them in Jackson, right, Hop?

12:42.375 --> 12:44.417
-The spic?
-Who popped Wesley?

12:44.500 --> 12:47.834
-Some hitter, right
outside my house.
-When was this?

12:48.500 --> 12:50.125
Last night,
early this morning.

12:50.208 --> 12:52.000
I kept calling him
and kept hearing
the ringer on his phone,

12:52.083 --> 12:54.750
like he was somewhere
in the house, but, you know,
like real sublevel,

12:54.834 --> 12:56.542
like, underneath
human hearing.

12:56.625 --> 12:58.125
Driving me
fucking nuts.

12:58.208 --> 13:00.041
And finally, I go out
to the driveway,

13:00.125 --> 13:02.709
and he's sprawled there,
face gone.

13:02.792 --> 13:05.458
You know, and at first,
I think, shit, a raccoon

13:05.542 --> 13:07.750
or some wild animal ate
his fucking face off.

13:07.834 --> 13:09.291
He's lying there
with my dry cleaning,

13:09.375 --> 13:11.208
which is splattered
with blood. (laughs)

13:11.291 --> 13:14.125
Smelled like a goddamn sewer,
he shit himself so bad.

13:15.250 --> 13:16.834
And nobody
heard nothing--

13:16.917 --> 13:18.250
not a single
neighbor in this

13:18.333 --> 13:19.959
quiet residential
block came out.

13:20.041 --> 13:22.083
No neighborhood watch,
nothing.

13:22.166 --> 13:25.000
-Where is my lighter?
-Can't smoke in here.

13:25.208 --> 13:27.041
Dad, special
circumstance.

13:27.125 --> 13:28.583
-Vivian doesn't like it.
-(scoffs)

13:28.667 --> 13:31.417
Now, you have any idea
who it was who did this?

13:31.959 --> 13:34.041
Who? I don't know,
I mean,

13:34.125 --> 13:35.834
shit, I thought
you'd tell me.

13:35.917 --> 13:38.792
Oh. This was
on my windshield.

13:38.875 --> 13:41.208
Letting me know
that he's watching me,
taunting me.

13:41.291 --> 13:44.250
-Wanting me to panic.
-Yeah, he's got you
panicked all right.

13:44.333 --> 13:46.083
But this is not what
a professional does.

13:46.166 --> 13:48.250
This, this feels personal.

13:48.333 --> 13:49.834
You think it was Salas?

13:49.917 --> 13:51.583
Junior:
(sighs) I mean,

13:51.667 --> 13:53.750
it could be. It's...

13:53.834 --> 13:56.333
There's a lot of moving parts
right now. It's all unclear--

13:56.417 --> 13:57.667
Just think. Think.

13:57.750 --> 13:59.250
-(sighs)
-You know, when
these things happen,

13:59.333 --> 14:00.417
you have a feeling
in your gut.

14:00.500 --> 14:02.542
The last few days,
what's been going on?

14:02.625 --> 14:05.166
(sighs, stammers)

14:05.250 --> 14:07.000
Who the fuck knows? It's...

14:07.083 --> 14:10.083
Albert Einstein wondered
if the moon would exist
if we weren't looking at it,

14:10.166 --> 14:12.542
and that Albert
fucking Einstein, Dad.

14:12.625 --> 14:16.083
(sighs) Let me ask
you something. You two, Jett.

14:16.500 --> 14:17.917
Anyone approach you
in the last couple weeks,

14:18.000 --> 14:19.709
-anything out
of the ordinary, Bennie?
-No.

14:19.792 --> 14:21.125
-Carl?
-No.

14:21.208 --> 14:23.208
Nobody who might be
a plant for Salas,

14:23.291 --> 14:25.458
asking questions, Jett?

14:25.542 --> 14:26.875
Not a soul.

14:26.959 --> 14:28.375
You sure about that?

14:28.458 --> 14:31.000
I-I'm not angry, I...

14:31.083 --> 14:33.500
I just wanna know if
anyone's been harassing you.

14:33.583 --> 14:35.500
I don't know Jacinto Salas.

14:35.583 --> 14:38.208
I have never spoken
to anyone who works for him

14:38.291 --> 14:41.583
or who might be a plant,
nor do I intend to, ever.

14:42.375 --> 14:44.667
