maybe you can pick up
some booze?

38:14.375 --> 38:16.166
Water.

38:16.250 --> 38:17.917
Drink lots of water.

38:37.875 --> 38:42.709
(helicopter whirring overhead)

38:44.041 --> 38:47.208
(police shouting indistinctly)

38:48.583 --> 38:50.834
(indistinct police radios
chattering)

38:53.250 --> 38:56.500
(helicopter whirring overhead)

39:05.750 --> 39:07.917
(thunder rumbling)

39:21.834 --> 39:24.375
You keep running,
I'm gonna shoot!

39:24.458 --> 39:26.375
-Jett!
-(panting)

39:27.500 --> 39:29.583
Hands where I can see them!

39:31.083 --> 39:32.333
Dennon?

39:32.417 --> 39:34.583
That's not my real name.

39:37.709 --> 39:39.959
Well, what is your name?

39:40.041 --> 39:41.542
Dillon.

39:41.625 --> 39:44.417
Jack Dillon. Now, come on,
I don't wanna shoot you.

39:45.667 --> 39:47.208
So, don't!

39:47.291 --> 39:49.583
Those paintings
were set up as bait.

39:50.125 --> 39:53.208
Part of a sting operation
for an art theft ring.

39:53.917 --> 39:56.875
I'm sorry you walked
into this. Now, turn around.

39:58.291 --> 40:00.375
You're not
taking me in.

40:00.458 --> 40:02.083
Hands on your head!

40:03.083 --> 40:04.333
I'm not armed.

40:04.417 --> 40:06.667
Then why are we arguing?
Hands on your head.

40:12.125 --> 40:13.542
(thunder rumbling)

40:18.792 --> 40:20.208
What are you doing?

40:22.208 --> 40:23.875
Don't make me shoot you.

40:25.125 --> 40:26.959
-(cocks gun)
-Stop.

40:27.291 --> 40:29.500
If I run, you're
gonna shoot me.

40:30.083 --> 40:31.875
If I walk back to you,

40:31.959 --> 40:33.834
you're gonna shoot me.

40:33.917 --> 40:36.667
So, you either wanna
shoot me no matter what,

40:38.208 --> 40:40.709
or you're not gonna
shoot me at all.

40:43.750 --> 40:46.834
♪ ♪

41:01.041 --> 41:03.250
You shoot
a lot of people?

41:04.458 --> 41:06.083
Hardly ever.

41:08.792 --> 41:11.125
Is that a gun on my balls?

41:11.542 --> 41:13.000
Thought you weren't armed.

41:13.083 --> 41:15.250
Forgot I had it.

41:15.333 --> 41:17.500
-Now look...
-(thunder rumbling)

41:17.583 --> 41:20.709
...I know this is not
personal for you.

41:20.792 --> 41:23.291
You're only
doing your job,

41:23.375 --> 41:25.417
but I'm not going to jail.

41:27.375 --> 41:30.667
I appreciate you not reminding
me I owe you my life.

41:32.875 --> 41:34.709
What's your idea?

41:36.375 --> 41:38.041
Put our guns down,

41:38.875 --> 41:40.583
go somewhere
and get a drink,

41:41.750 --> 41:43.000
start over.

41:43.083 --> 41:47.041
(thunder rumbling)

41:49.709 --> 41:52.792
♪ ♪

42:05.166 --> 42:06.500
(sighs)

42:07.875 --> 42:09.417
How long you been up?

42:09.917 --> 42:11.583
Who says I slept?

42:13.125 --> 42:14.667
You were out cold
in the middle of the night

42:14.750 --> 42:16.458
when I went down
to the lobby.

42:17.875 --> 42:20.709
Was that to call your
superiors, report on me?

42:21.917 --> 42:24.333
Can neither confirm nor deny.

42:24.750 --> 42:27.583
What were you wearing,
a towel?

42:34.959 --> 42:36.834
Did you hide
my clothes?

42:36.917 --> 42:39.375
I can neither
confirm nor deny.

42:43.000 --> 42:45.625
This isn't like
a bribe, is it?

42:45.709 --> 42:47.333
-Who's bribing who?
-You know what I'm saying.

42:47.417 --> 42:49.291
People do that,
trade information.

42:49.375 --> 42:51.625
Is that what we're trading,
information?

42:53.208 --> 42:55.750
-Okay, let me ask you something.
-Fire away.

42:55.834 --> 42:57.458
Are we allowed to talk
about our work?

42:57.542 --> 42:59.583
Is it important
we talk at all?

43:00.291 --> 43:03.000
Sounds a little forward
when you put it like that.

43:03.083 --> 43:05.041
Yes, slippery slope.

43:05.583 --> 43:06.917
But if I was a guy--

43:07.000 --> 43:09.125
I probably
wouldn't be here.

43:09.208 --> 43:10.333
(chuckles)

43:10.792 --> 43:12.709
If a guy said,

43:12.792 --> 43:14.709
"why don't we quit talking
about it and get a room..."

43:14.792 --> 43:17.667
On a first date, could come
off a little insensitive.

43:17.750 --> 43:18.959
-Too fast.
-Too eager.

43:19.041 --> 43:22.250
-Too uncomplicated.
-You're not uncomplicated.

43:22.333 --> 43:24.000
I strike you as
a complicated girl?

43:24.083 --> 43:26.375
You strike me
as no girl I've ever met.

43:31.083 --> 43:32.625
Question.

43:32.709 --> 43:35.417
-You ask a lot of questions.
-Well, I don't know
a lot of things.

43:35.500 --> 43:39.125
Is this what you always
wanted to do when you grew up?

43:39.709 --> 43:41.125
-Yes.
-Come on.

43:41.208 --> 43:44.125
-Ever since I can remember.
-I find that hard to believe.

43:44.208 --> 43:45.834
Scout's honor.

43:46.250 --> 43:47.917
Other little
girls wanted to be

43:48.041 --> 43:51.583
princesses, get married,
become a vet, a teacher.

43:52.500 --> 43:54.875
My best friend
in fourth grade was convinced

43:54.959 --> 43:57.750
she could study to be
a mermaid when she grew up.

43:58.875 --> 44:00.041
Not me.

44:00.750 --> 44:03.750
I always dreamed of breaking
into places and stealing things.

44:03.834 --> 44:06.375
Getting a job was
never an option?

44:06.709 --> 44:08.458
You think I do
this as a hobby?

44:08.542 --> 44:10.875
Big blocks of cash
are hard to come by
in a credit economy.

44:10.959 --> 44:12.875
It's a full-time job
finding things to steal.

44:12.959 --> 44:14.041
Well, you know
what I mean.

44:14.125 --> 44:16.291
Puts food on your table.

44:17.667 --> 44:19.542
-Hmm.
-How about you?

44:20.291 --> 44:22.291
You like sending
people to jail?

44:22.834 --> 44:25.041
-It's what I do.
-Not what I asked.

44:26.333 --> 44:28.750
Well, doesn't bother me.

44:30.083 --> 44:31.500
If it did,
I'd do something else.

44:31.583 --> 44:33.000
You always wanted to be a cop?

44:33.583 --> 44:37.500
No, but I guess I always liked
solving stuff. I like puzzles.

44:37.583 --> 44:39.959
-Hmm.
-Mysteries.

44:40.542 --> 44:42.709
It's what I do all day long.

44:44.083 --> 44:46.792
Some more perplexing
than others.

44:48.333 --> 44:49.583
Last question.

44:50.709 --> 44:52.083
Is that loaded?

44:54.709 --> 44:56.375
Sure, why carry it otherwise?

44:56.458 --> 44:59.166
Not that. That.

45:00.875 --> 45:02.709
Might be between
your legs, but...

45:03.792 --> 45:05.458
it belongs to me.

45:07.166 --> 45:10.083
(phone buzzing)

45:10.166 --> 45:11.500
Hey.

45:12.375 --> 45:14.583
Well done.
Let's talk tomorrow.

45:15.333 --> 45:17.000
Where you headed?

45:18.041 --> 45:19.583
Sounds good.

45:19.667 --> 45:21.333
Can you put her on?

45:22.375 --> 45:23.750
Hi, monkey.

45:24.291 --> 45:25.959
How was your field trip?

45:26.959 --> 45:28.291
Mm-hmm.

45:29.041 --> 45:30.625
No kidding.

45:31.041 --> 45:33.250
You have a good eye for detail.

45:34.792 --> 45:37.166
(TV playing indistinctly)

45:37.917 --> 45:39.125
(turns off TV)

45:41.250 --> 45:44.625
I thought maybe...
you took off.

45:52.583 --> 45:54.000
Where's your wife?

45:55.500 --> 45:57.125
Threw me out.

46:00.166 --> 46:02.875
This before or after
Josie was murdered?

46:05.417 --> 46:07.000
(sighs) Today.

46:07.583 --> 46:10.875
(sighs) When I told her
she deserved way better than me.

46:14.083 --> 46:16.125
That's a cowardly thing to say.

46:17.375 --> 46:19.750
Makes it sound like it's her
fault she's not doing better.

46:19.834 --> 46:21.583
Dillon:
It doesn't matter
what it sounded like.

46:21.667 --> 46:23.834
I had to set her free.

46:24.500 --> 46:27.208
Set her free by
admitting to the affair

46:27.291 --> 46:29.417
after your girlfriend
is already dead.

46:30.417 --> 46:33.959
-The only reason to do that--
-Is if you're not coming back.
Well, I didn't think I was.

46:38.792 --> 46:41.000
-I can't understand that.
-Of course not.

46:41.083 --> 46:42.959
You always have to have a plan.

46:43.041 --> 46:45.291
A contingency,
ways in, ways out.

46:45.375 --> 46:46.750
Yes.

46:46.834 --> 46:49.375
Isn't the whole point
to control events?

46:49.458 --> 46:51.667
They're still gonna get
away from you if that's
what's gonna happen.

46:51.750 --> 46:53.709
Why make things worse?

46:53.792 --> 46:55.417
I'm dead, Jett.

46:56.375 --> 46:57.959
I'm not supposed to be here.

46:59.125 --> 47:00.458
This is...

47:00.542 --> 47:02.166
A dream?

47:04.208 --> 47:06.417
Yeah, it could be.

47:08.417 --> 47:10.291
My imagination is
less than stellar.

47:10.375 --> 47:12.625
Could be this is
all I came up with.

47:12.709 --> 47:15.208
But, hey, the company
couldn't be better.

47:20.208 --> 47:22.208
Let's talk
about you.

47:24.250 --> 47:26.333
What's your move?

47:29.667 --> 47:32.959
You got to tell Charlie
about Junior and Salas.

47:33.583 --> 47:35.333
Timing is a little off now.

47:35.417 --> 47:37.417
Well, it won't be that
hard to get him proof.

47:37.917 --> 47:39.792
I mean, I don't know that
I could get it, seeing as how

47:39.875 --> 47:41.583
I'll get arrested if
I step out that door,

47:41.667 --> 47:43.709
but we can figure
something out.

47:43.792 --> 47:45.667
I killed his son.

47:45.750 --> 47:47.000
Junior was
out of control.

47:47.083 --> 47:49.959
Deep down, Charlie knows
that, and he likes you.

47:50.041 --> 47:52.750
Charlie will never
forgive this.

47:54.250 --> 47:56.208
I wouldn't, would you?

48:01.083 --> 48:04.500
(phone buzzing)

48:05.000 --> 48:06.542
Who is it?

48:06.625 --> 48:09.375
(sighs) My second favorite
person in the world.

48:16.333 --> 48:19.250
-Yes.
-Evans (over phone):
We need to sit down and talk.

48:19.625 --> 48:22.834
I'm kind of busy right now.
I just got back into town,

48:22.917 --> 48:24.834
as you well know.

48:24.917 --> 48:27.625
I need a little downtime
in between these jobs.

48:27.709 --> 48:29.208
Things have changed.

48:29.291 --> 48:30.792
Remember how
I informed you that

48:30.875 --> 48:34.250
he expected two more jobs from
you before erasing your debt?

48:35.000 --> 48:36.250
I remember.

48:36.333 --> 48:38.917
Well, he's willing to cut
it down to one final job,

48:39.000 --> 48:41.125
provided you act quickly.

48:41.208 --> 48:42.750
What changed his mind?

48:42.834 --> 48:46.917
He needs you to take care
of a problem, make it
go away, ASAP.

48:47.000 --> 48:50.709
Charlie Baudelaire,
and then you're all done.

48:51.542 --> 48:55.542
I thought I made it very clear,
that is not what I do.

48:55.625 --> 48:57.959
If you're in the business
of killing people,

48:58.041 --> 49:00.583
you should go hire
professional killers.

49:00.667 --> 49:02.709
I explained that to my boss.

49:04.166 --> 49:07.542
Well, explain it to him
so he understands this time.

49:07.625 --> 49:10.834
-Maybe you should tell him.
-What was that?

49:10.917 --> 49:14.834
I said, maybe you should
inform him of this yourself.

49:14.917 --> 49:16.000
Let me put him on.

49:16.083 --> 49:19.667
-Bestic is here?
-Right beside me. Hold on.

49:22.792 --> 49:24.417
Everything okay?

49:25.375 --> 49:27.208
Bestic (over phone):
Daisy Kowalski.

49:27.291 --> 49:29.166
I understand you
just returned from

49:29.250 --> 49:31.417
being away from
your daughter.

49:32.291 --> 49:34.709
I just landed
in town myself.

49:34.792 --> 49:36.083
Business.

49:36.166 --> 49:39.458
Schedule's gone haywire
over a delicate matter.

49:40.500 --> 49:44.125
I have limited time, but I can
carve out a moment to sit down,

49:45.250 --> 49:47.083
face-to-face,

49:47.166 --> 49:51.500
so we can discuss
your apprehension
to this final task.

49:52.083 --> 49:54.792
You've performed
so well, Daisy.

49:55.583 --> 49:57.458
I think it would
be shameful

49:57.542 --> 50:00.291
to now disrespect
our agreement.

50:00.375 --> 50:03.417
And I think you have the wrong
person for this last job.

50:03.500 --> 50:05.667
Be that as it may...

50:06.750 --> 50:09.166
let's meet somewhere
very public,

50:09.250 --> 50:11.041
say tomorrow
morning,

50:11.125 --> 50:13.083
somewhere you
feel safe,

50:13.166 --> 50:15.083
and I can have my
back to the wall.

50:15.166 --> 50:17.375
Literally, not
metaphorically.

50:18.959 --> 50:21.542
The restaurant
at Hotel Josephine.

50:23.375 --> 50:25.000
Come alone.

50:25.750 --> 50:28.375
Breakfast, 9:00 a.m.

50:32.583 --> 50:34.250
Sleep tight, Daisy.

50:35.625 --> 50:37.166
(line clicks)

50:46.291 --> 50:49.417
♪ ♪

51:16.125 --> 51:19.208
♪ ♪

51:46.166 --> 51:48.000
♪ ♪

52:18.041 --> 52:19.291
♪ ♪

52:35.542 --> 52:37.083
♪ ("JETT" THEME PLAYS) ♪

52:37.291 --> 52:38.166
Yes.

52:38.250 --> 52:39.375
MILAN BESTIC: Charlie?

52:40.333 --> 52:41.750
CHARLIE BAUDELAIRE:
How'd you get this number?

52:41.834 --> 52:43.250
BESTIC:
I heard about your son.

52:43.667 --> 52:45.417
I have a proposition for you.

52:47.000 --> 52:48.875
MAN: You've taken a lot
of chances walking in here.

52:49.208 --> 52:50.542
JETT:
I don't have a lot of options.

52:50.834 --> 52:53.208
You're a girl who's used
to calling her own shots,
aren't you?

52:53.291 --> 52:54.417
JETT:
How'd you pick up on that?

52:54.625 --> 52:56.333
BESTIC:
Did you honestly think
that I would walk

52:56.417 --> 52:59.458
into a situation with you
without taking out insurance?

53:00.667 --> 53:02.917
You were too blind to see it.

53:04.583 --> 53:06.208
JETT:
I came here to tell you,

53:06.417 --> 53:07.959
(ALARM WAILS)

53:08.208 --> 53:10.583
I will not do what you
ask me to do.

53:11.959 --> 53:13.125
We're done.

53:14.125 --> 53:15.542
BESTIC:
We are not done.

53:16.250 --> 53:19.583
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

53:20.959 --> 53:22.333
-♪ (MUSIC PLAYS) ♪
-AGENT: Who's this?

53:22.417 --> 53:23.458
AGENT 2:
Never seen him before.

53:23.834 --> 53:25.417
Is he showing them a badge?

53:26.417 --> 53:27.417
(GUNSHOT)

53:27.625 --> 53:28.834
SEBASTIAN GUTIERREZ: I think
episode eight is where

53:29.041 --> 53:30.834
it's revealed that Charlie
really is not in control.

53:30.917 --> 53:31.709
Dad.

53:32.333 --> 53:34.333
We have seen that Junior has
pretty much hijacked our story.

53:34.417 --> 53:36.291
He is completely unpredictable.

53:36.583 --> 53:38.291
I'm regrouping, is what.

53:38.500 --> 53:41.125
I mean you always say,
come to you first. Come to you.

53:41.208 --> 53:42.375
So, I'm here.

53:42.458 --> 53:44.333
By turning a blind eye
to his son,

53:44.625 --> 53:46.667
he has lost
basically everything he had.

53:46.875 --> 53:48.417
But this is not
what a professional does,

53:48.500 --> 53:50.250
This-- this feels personal.

53:50.333 --> 53:51.709
You know, there are
so many stories that are

53:51.792 --> 53:54.125
about the sins of the fathers
become the sins of the sons.

53:54.208 --> 53:56.458
And in a strange way,
this is the opposite.

53:57.250 --> 53:59.375
'Cause you can't be
a cold-blooded ruthless killer

53:59.458 --> 54:02.125
if there is somebody that
you're really worried about.

54:02.750 --> 54:05.125
And that is both Jett
and Charlie's problem,

54:05.208 --> 54:06.542
that things are going to come
to a head

54:06.625 --> 54:08.250
where we're going to have
in the same room

54:08.333 --> 54:10.792
Charlie, Junior, Jett,

54:11.083 --> 54:13.041
and Dylan is gonna walk in.

54:13.291 --> 54:14.250
He's a cop.

54:14.333 --> 54:16.041
Well haven't you strayed
a long fucking way

54:16.125 --> 54:19.166
from your reservation,
Detective Dylan.

54:20.333 --> 54:23.667
Jett knows that she should stay
out of this,

54:23.834 --> 54:26.542
but she can't sit there
and watch.

54:26.625 --> 54:29.542
(GRUNTING)

54:30.375 --> 54:31.542
(GUNSHOT)

54:33.000 --> 54:33.834
Junior.

54:34.125 --> 54:36.208
You know she doesn't make a lot
of bad decisions.

54:36.500 --> 54:38.333
And this one is one of those.

54:38.750 --> 54:39.750
Junior.

54:40.333 --> 54:43.333
-(YELLING) My name is Charles--
-(GUNSHOT)

54:43.417 --> 54:46.000
CARLA GUGINO: I mean,
the moment Jett kills Junior,

54:46.166 --> 54:48.375
there's no way Charlie will ever
be able to forgive her.

54:48.667 --> 54:51.166
So, at that moment she knows
that that relationship

54:51.250 --> 54:52.667
is never gonna be
what it was.

54:53.291 --> 54:54.542
JETT: Charlie...

54:56.959 --> 54:58.083
I'm sorry.

54:59.083 --> 55:01.458
GUGINO:
Ultimately, her killing Junior
to protect Dylan

55:01.542 --> 55:03.208
is just a bad idea.

55:03.625 --> 55:04.834
We gotta go.

55:05.542 --> 55:08.709
So, this is the unspooling
of the thread, for sure.

55:12.709 --> 55:14.583
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪
